ernate tool-call syntax. Do not quote or place tool-call markup inside explanatory text; when you decide to call the tool, emit the tool call itself.\nIf you use MOUSE, include integer row and col arguments.\nEFFICIENCY BUDGET \u2014 your score on each level is (baseline_actions / your_actions)^2, so every wasted action costs you quadratically.\nLevel 1: you have used 3 of about 39 target actions so far.", "kind": "tool", "inContext": true}, {"label": "THINKING", "content": "DOWN moved the blue rectangle from (16,16)-(19,35) to (20,16)-(23,35) - that's a shift of +4 rows. So each move shifts the blue rectangle by 4 cells in the direction pressed.\nCurrent blue position: (20,16)-(23,35), size 4x20\nYellow arches at rows 52-59\nThe blue rectangle is 4 rows tall. Each DOWN moves it 4 rows. To reach row 52, I need to go from row 20 to row 52, which is 32 rows = 8 DOWN moves. But I should first figure out what the goal is.\nLet me think about what the goal might be:\n1. Navigate to the yellow arches (like goals/ports)\n2. Navigate to the charcoal/magenta area at top\n3. Something else\nLet me try moving the blue rectangle to one of the yellow arches to see what happens. The left yellow arch is at cols 16-27 (with a gap in the middle), and the right one is at cols 40-51. The blue rectangle is 20 cols wide, so it's quite large.\nActually, let me reconsider. The yellow shapes are U-shaped (arches with open tops). Maybe the goal is to fit the blue rectangle through one of them? Or maybe the goal is to reach the top where the charcoal and magenta objects are?\nLet me try moving UP to go back towards the top and see if the blue rectangle can interact with the charcoal/magenta objects.\nActually, let me first try to understand the game better. The blue rectangle started at (16,12)-(19,31). The charcoal is at (1,36)-(3,39) and magenta at (4,36)-(7,39). These are at the top right area.\nLet me try moving the blue rectangle to overlap with the magenta object and see what happens. 